      • send

        public final StreamSinkFrameChannel send(WebSocketFrameType type,
                                         long payloadSize)
                                  throws IOException
        Returns a new StreamSinkFrameChannel for sending the given WebSocketFrameType with the given payload. If this method is called multiple times, subsequent StreamSinkFrameChannel's will not be writable until all previous frames were completely written.
        Parameters:
        type - The WebSocketFrameType for which a StreamSinkChannel should be created
        payloadSize - The size of the payload which will be included in the WebSocket Frame. This may be 0 if you want to transmit no payload at all.
        Throws:
        IOException
